# Magic 8-Ball Team Chat — Project Rules

## What This App Is

A satirical Microsoft Teams–style single-page app. Sidebar of fake coworker DMs, typing indicators, incoming-call popup with ringtone, and a fake group video call grid. The humor is corporate jargon, mild gaslighting, PM pressure, and absurdist workplace culture. It is not a real productivity tool.

**Deploy path:** Vite base URL `/magic-8-ball/` — all asset paths must respect this.

---

## Architecture — Two Layers, Keep Them Separate

### 1. Orchestration Layer (stays in TypeScript/code — do NOT move to LLM)
These mechanics are scripted. They must remain deterministic and fast:
- Which character is "speaking" at any time
- Typing indicator timing (show → delay → hide → render reply)
- Ninja PM incoming-call popup trigger (fires on every user message in Ninja PM chat)
- Every-4th-message global badge / PM follow-up injection
- Group chat unlock (only after call-answer flow completes)
- Message sound playback
- Easter egg detection: if user input matches `/who made this( app)?/i`, bypass LLM entirely and return the hardcoded credit link (`rickthewebdev.com`)

### 2. Copy Layer (swap static arrays → LLM calls)
These character response lines should reference the user's actual message while staying in-persona. This is where the LLM lives:
- **Synergy Bot** — secretly picks a bucket (yes / no / maybe / ghosted) in code, then passes that outcome to the LLM as a hidden constraint. The LLM phrases the reply; it does not pick the outcome.
- **Ninja PM** — reply text and PM follow-up injections
- **Scapegoat** — excuse generation
- **Growth Guru** — motivational / pivot lines
- **Group Chat** — corporate jargon replies attributed to Ninja PM
- **Meme Guy** — still static image cycle; no LLM (images, not text)

