## Mechanics Checklist (Never Break These)

- [ ] Typing indicator always appears before any reply, with a character-appropriate delay
- [ ] Ninja PM's "Please join the call." + call popup fires on every Ninja PM user message
- [ ] Global message counter increments on every user send (all chats)
- [ ] Every 4th user message: inject PM follow-up into Ninja PM thread, play new-message sound, increment badge
- [ ] Meme Guy never calls the LLM — returns next unused meme filename, cycles after all 30 used
- [ ] Group chat is locked until call answer flow completes; after unlock it stays unlocked for the session
- [ ] Easter egg (`/who made this( app)?/i`) returns hardcoded credit regardless of active chat
- [ ] Synergy Bot outcome (yes/no/maybe/ghosted) is selected by code, passed to LLM as hidden constraint
- [ ] All audio requires user interaction before first play (browser autoplay policy)
- [ ] Vite base URL `/magic-8-ball/` — no hardcoded absolute paths

---

## TypeScript Conventions

- Strict mode on. No `any`.
- Character configs typed with a shared `CharacterConfig` interface (id, name, avatar, systemPrompt, fallbackLines, typingDelayMs)
- LLM call wrappers return `Promise<string>` — caller doesn't need to know the transport
- State lives in hooks or Zustand (whichever is already set up) — not scattered in components

---

## UI/UX Rules

- Match Teams aesthetic closely enough to be recognizable as a parody — sidebar, chat bubbles, presence dots, badge counters
- Typing indicator: animated dots, not a spinner
- Call popup: blocks interaction, has ringtone, Answer / Decline buttons
- Video grid: 2×3 grid of fake tiles (Ninja PM, Synergy Bot, Growth Guru, You, Blue Sky, Goose) — tiles are static avatars/names, no real video
- Dark mode: match whatever Teams uses — dark sidebar, slightly lighter chat area
- No real loading spinners during LLM calls — the typing indicator IS the loading state

---

## What NOT to Do

- Do not let the LLM pick the Synergy Bot outcome — code picks it, LLM only phrases it
- Do not send full chat history to the LLM — last user message + system prompt only
- Do not break the 4-message PM nag logic when refactoring the message counter
- Do not add new characters without a corresponding `src/characters/` file and entry in `messageRouter.ts`
- Do not use `alert()`, `confirm()`, or `prompt()` — all UI lives in the component layer
- Do not hardcode meme filenames in components — import from `src/data/memes.ts`
- Do not expose the LLM system prompt in the client bundle in plaintext if using a server route

---

## Adding a New Feature — Standard Checklist

1. Does it involve a new character? → New file in `src/characters/`, update `messageRouter.ts`
2. Does it involve new orchestration logic? → `src/orchestration/`, not inside a component
3. Does it call the LLM? → Add guardrails paragraph to system prompt, set max_tokens ≤ 120, add static fallback
4. Does it play audio? → Check browser autoplay policy, gate on prior user interaction
5. Does it add UI? → Component only, no business logic inside
6. Does it change global state? → Update the relevant hook or store, document side effects here

---

## Humor Guardrails (Design Intent)

The comedy target is: **absurdist corporate satire**. Think Office Space, not Succession. The characters should feel like archetypes everyone has worked with, not attacks on real people.

- Punching up (at processes, jargon, corporate theater): ✅
- Punching sideways (at recognizable workplace archetypes): ✅ if not tied to protected characteristics
- Punching down (at real individuals, groups, identities): ❌ always
- Anything that would make a real HR team take action: ❌ always
- Breaking the fourth wall to explain the joke: ❌ always — stay in character
